The course deals with main 20th century theoretical approaches of  power, communication, ideology and discourse, wellknown authorities (Dijk, Laclau, Schmitt, Reis etc) and links between their thoughts and ideas. Comparing concepts like: ideology,  politics, discourse,  , power, communication etc. Main idea to explore how in contemporary media age power relation are  established through communication, "soft power" 
In homeworks students are required to exert learned skills for the analyses of concrete sociopolitical phenomena.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main purpose of this course is to develop skills for analysing and comprehending contemporary sociopolitical phenomena. Throughout the course the students will read and discuss topics like identity and ideology; political communication; discourse and ideology; concept of power ; semiotic mechanism of constructing identities etc.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will be able to: 
1) identify and analyse the signifying, symbolic and ideological systems;
2) understand the role of communication in establishing social relations;
3) define semiotic aspects of sociopolitical research and describe relations between these;
4) define the major paradigms, theories, and concepts in 20th century theoretical approaches of power ;
5) apply critical reading and analytical skills to various academic and non-academic texts;
6) express personal theoretical preferences and defend them by constructing evidence-based arguments.
7) develop the skills of team work
